description: "The chemical reactions and pathways involving organonitrogen compound." [GOC:pr, GOC:TermGenie]
name: organonitrogen compound metabolic process

description: "The chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein. Includes protein modification." [GOC:ma]
name: protein metabolic process

description: "The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of organonitrogen compound." [GOC:pr, GOC:TermGenie]
name: organonitrogen compound biosynthetic process

description: "The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of organic and inorganic nitrogenous compounds." [GOC:jl, ISBN:0198506732]
name: cellular nitrogen compound biosynthetic process

description: "The cellular metabolic process in which a protein is formed, using the sequence of a mature mRNA or circRNA molecule to specify the sequence of amino acids in a polypeptide chain. Translation is mediated by the ribosome, and begins with the formation of a ternary complex between aminoacylated initiator methionine tRNA, GTP, and initiation factor 2, which subsequently associates with the small subunit of the ribosome and an mRNA or circRNA. Translation ends with the release of a polypeptide chain from the ribosome." [GOC:go_curators]
name: translation

description: "A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits; includes transport to the sites of protein synthesis." [GOC:ma, PMID:26404467, Wikipedia:Ribosome_biogenesis]
name: ribosome biogenesis

description: "The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of peptides, compounds of 2 or more (but usually less than 100) amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another. This may include the translation of a precursor protein and its subsequent processing into a functional peptide." [GOC:dph, GOC:jl]
name: peptide biosynthetic process

description: "The chemical reactions and pathways involving peptides, compounds of two or more amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another." [GOC:go_curators]
name: peptide metabolic process

description: "The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of an amide, any derivative of an oxoacid in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group." [GOC:curators]
name: amide biosynthetic process

description: "The chemical reactions and pathways involving an amide, any derivative of an oxoacid in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group, as carried out by individual cells." [GOC:curators]
name: amide metabolic process
